+
+## Essential-Feature Ledger
+
+| Feature | Classification | Step verdict |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| stage order | `essential` | `[VERIFIED]` Tao's mechanism is an ordered delayed-abrupt-transfer chain, not a generic sparse graph; sources: `atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md`, `atlas-anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall-FINAL-REPORT.md` |
+| delayed-threshold behavior | `essential` | `[VERIFIED]` the final report names delayed threshold activation as load-bearing, and the trigger-crossing timing is explicit in the mechanism reconstruction; sources: `atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md`, `atlas-anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall-FINAL-REPORT.md` |
+| pump / amplifier / rotor / next-shell role hierarchy | `essential` | `[VERIFIED]` the five causal roles are the exact mechanism-level object later exact-NS tests must track; sources: `atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md`, `atlas-anatomy-exploration-002-REPORT.md` |
+| amplitude hierarchy | `essential` | `[INFERRED]` the literal Tao coefficients are not frozen as formulas, but the weak-seed / strong-amplifier / stronger-rotor / delayed-transfer hierarchy is required for Tao-likeness; sources: `atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md`, `atlas-anatomy-exploration-002-REPORT.md`, `judgments/chain-01.md` |
+| tiny-trigger role | `essential` | `[VERIFIED]` the inherited packet explicitly says the tiny trigger `X3,n` is mechanism-central while initially negligible; sources: `atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md`, `atlas-anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall-FINAL-REPORT.md` |
+| admissible leakage | `open but load-bearing` | `[VERIFIED]` the mission and winning chain require quantitative leakage language, but no single functional or threshold is yet frozen; sources: `atlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-MISSION.md`, `CHAIN.md`, `planner-chains/chain-02.md` |
+| time-scale separation | `essential` | `[VERIFIED]` the mechanism depends on shell-to-shell transfer times shrinking while amplitudes stay comparably active; sources: `atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md`, `atlas-anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall-FINAL-REPORT.md` |
+| phase sensitivity | `open but load-bearing` | `[INFERRED]` the planning attack correctly identifies phase as part of the missing exact-NS object discipline, even though Step 1 does not inherit one final phase gauge; sources: `attacks/chain-01.md`, `judgments/chain-01.md` |
+| helical-sign sensitivity | `open but load-bearing` | `[INFERRED]` the exact setting is explicitly Fourier/helical and the surviving mismatch is written in geometry- and helicity-sensitive terms, but Step 1 only freezes the requirement that sign sheets be declared canonically; sources: `atlas-anatomy-exploration-002-REPORT.md`, `CHAIN.md`, `judgments/chain-01.md` |
+| support semantics | `essential` | `[INFERRED]` Step 1 exists partly to decide whether support means modes, conjugate pairs, or packets; leaving that unfrozen would make later robustness work circular; sources: `GOAL.md`, `CHAIN.md`, `judgments/chain-01.md` |
+| literal five-scalar coordinates `(a,b,c,d,ã)` | `dispensable` | `[INFERRED]` the mission must preserve roles, not Tao's notation; sources: `atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md` |
+| Tao's exact numerical coefficient formulas | `dispensable` as formulas, but not as hierarchy | `[INFERRED]` Step 2 need not import the exact averaged-model constants, but it must preserve the hierarchy those constants encode; sources: `atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md`, `atlas-anatomy-exploration-002-REPORT.md` |
+
+## Canonical Packet-Language Memo
+
+- `[INFERRED]` **Packet object.**
+  The branch will count a packet object as a finite role-labeled helical packet,
+  not as a single bare Fourier mode and not as a bare conjugate pair.
+- `[INFERRED]` **Support semantics.**
+  `support` means the role-labeled helical packet together with the exact
+  forced conjugate completion required to realize a real-valued velocity field.
+- `[INFERRED]` **Conjugate completion.**
+  Real-valuedness forces conjugate completion at the canonical representation
+  level, but conjugate completion is not the primary notion of packet identity.
+  Packet identity lives at the role-labeled helical-packet level.
+- `[VERIFIED]` **Why not single-mode semantics.**
+  The local record explicitly says exact NS bookkeeping depends on more than a
+  support graph: conjugate mirrors, full `p+q=k` closure, helical signs, and
+  exact projection all matter; sources:
+  `atlas-anatomy-exploration-002-REPORT.md`, `judgments/chain-01.md`,
+  `planner.md`.
+- `[INFERRED]` **Canonicalization policy.**
+  Later robustness audits must fix in advance:
+  one conjugate-representative convention,
+  one helical basis convention,
+  one role-label ordering,
+  one amplitude normalization anchor,
+  and one phase anchor or equivalent canonical gauge.
+- `[INFERRED]` **Cosmetic representation changes.**
+  Once that policy is fixed, reordering labels or displaying the mandatory
+  conjugate packet explicitly versus implicitly is cosmetic.
+- `[VERIFIED]` **Substantive modeling changes.**
+  Packet regrouping, switching support semantics, retuning time windows or
+  thresholds, changing helical sign sheets, or changing phase bookkeeping are
+  substantive modeling choices, not cosmetic canonicalization; sources:
+  `attacks/chain-01.md`, `judgments/chain-01.md`, `judgments/chain-03.md`.
+
+## Scope-Lock Sheet
+
+### Packet Semantics And Representation Commitments
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Later steps must work with finite role-labeled helical packets.
+- `[INFERRED]` Every promoted notion must use the same canonical conjugate
+  completion rule for real-valuedness.
+- `[INFERRED]` Every promoted notion must declare its helical sign sheet,
+  amplitude normalization, and phase anchor up front.
+- `[INFERRED]` No later step may change packet regrouping or support semantics
+  by convenience and still claim to be testing the same object.
+
+### Allowed Leakage / Behavioral Threshold Language
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Later candidate notions may use either leakage language or
+  behavioral-threshold language, because the winning chain explicitly leaves
+  both open; sources: `CHAIN.md`, `winning-chain.md`.
+- `[INFERRED]` But any such language must be:
+  quantitative,
+  attached to the frozen packet semantics above,
+  declared on one fixed finite time window or activation window,
+  normalized in one fixed canonical representation,
+  and immune to after-the-fact threshold retuning.
+- `[INFERRED]` Pure slogans such as "NS has too much coupling" or
+  "the packet looks sparse" are disallowed as threshold language.
+
+### Downstream-Gate Rule
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Every promoted notion in Chain Step 2 must name exactly one
+  downstream gate:
+  either one invariant dynamical observable on one stated packet family and time
+  window,
+  or one invariant admissibility sheet for adversarial exact search; sources:
+  `CHAIN.md`, `final-decider.md`.
+
+### Allowed Negative-Failure Buckets
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Final negative conclusions must land in exactly one bucket:
+  `not well-defined`,
+  `not robust after canonicalization`,
+  or `not useful for the target theorem or counterexample question`;
+  sources: `CHAIN.md`, `winning-chain.md`, `final-decider.md`.
+
+## Tao-Likeness Discriminator
+
+Later steps should count a packet family as Tao-like only if all of the
+following survive after canonicalization:
+
+1. `[VERIFIED]` The family contains identifiable carrier, delay-clock,
+   tiny-trigger, transfer-conduit, and next-stage carrier roles.
+2. `[VERIFIED]` Those roles interact in the ordered delayed-threshold sequence
+   inherited from Tao's mechanism, rather than merely in an arbitrary sparse
+   triad network.
+3. `[INFERRED]` The dominant channels realize a genuine hierarchy:
+   weak clock pump,
+   much smaller seed,
+   stronger post-threshold amplifier/rotor action,
+   and delayed next-stage transfer.
+4. `[INFERRED]` Phase data and helical sign bookkeeping are declared tightly
+   enough that the claimed hierarchy is not a representation artifact.
+5. `[INFERRED]` Spectator interactions stay within one predeclared admissible
+   leakage or behavioral screen on one predeclared finite time window.
+
+Negative discriminator:
+
+- `[INFERRED]` A family that is only sparse, multiscale, mirror-complete, or
+  triad-engineered, but has no delayed-threshold trigger logic or no honest
+  near-isolation screen, does **not** count as Tao-like for this branch.
+
+## Step Verdict
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Chain Step 2 is now well-posed.
+- `[INFERRED]` The exact frozen commitments Step 2 must inherit are:
+  - the essential-feature ledger above;
+  - packet-level helical support semantics with mandatory conjugate completion;
+  - explicit helical sign, amplitude, and phase bookkeeping;
+  - a predeclared leakage or behavioral threshold on a fixed finite window;
+  - the one-downstream-gate rule;
+  - and the three allowed final negative-failure buckets.
+- `[INFERRED]` No third exploration was needed:
+  the two completed explorations already froze the Step-1 object sharply enough
+  to start definition work without object-level drift.
+
+## Frozen Commitments For Chain Step 2
+
+- Later candidate notions must live on finite role-labeled helical packets with
+  mandatory conjugate completion in one fixed canonical representation.
+- Later candidate notions must preserve Tao's delayed-threshold role ledger,
+  including stage order, tiny-trigger centrality, amplitude hierarchy, and
+  time-scale separation.
+- Later candidate notions may use leakage or behavioral criteria, but only with
+  predeclared normalization, time window, and downstream gate.
+- Later negative conclusions may say only:
+  `not well-defined`,
+  `not robust after canonicalization`,
+  or `not useful for the target theorem or counterexample question`.
